---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
import { existsSync } from 'node:fs';

const cvPdfHref = '/files/sailesh_conjeti_cv.pdf';
const hasCvPdf = existsSync('public/files/sailesh_conjeti_cv.pdf');
---

<BaseLayout
  title="CV"
  description="Public-safe CV summary for Sailesh Conjeti."
>
  <Section title="Professional Summary">
    <div class="item">
      <p>
        Medical AI researcher and digital health product leader working at the intersection of
        medical image computing, clinical workflow AI, and deployable software systems.
      </p>
      <p>
        The profile reflects a path from academic medical imaging research to industry leadership
        and teaching in generative and agentic AI.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section title="Current Roles">
    <div class="list">
      <article class="item">
        <h3>Olympus EMEA (publicly reported)</h3>
        <p>
          Endoscopy workflow AI leadership focused on workflow-oriented clinical software and
          applied AI integration.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="item">
        <h3>Hamburg University of Applied Sciences</h3>
        <p>
          Staff/instructor role, including teaching in Generative and Agentic AI (2025-2026
          elective activity referenced in public sources).
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section title="Previous Experience">
    <div class="list">
      <article class="item">
        <h3>Siemens Healthineers</h3>
        <p>
          Medical AI and digital health product leadership across radiology and reporting-oriented
          AI programs.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="item">
        <h3>DeepMI / DZNE-Associated Postdoctoral Research</h3>
        <p>
          Postdoctoral work following PhD, focused on medical image computing and translational AI
          research.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="item">
        <h3>Academic Research Track</h3>
        <p>
          Contributions across neuroimaging, OCT/IVUS analysis, retrieval methods, segmentation
          quality control, and computational pathology.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section title="Education">
    <div class="list">
      <article class="item">
        <p>PhD in Medical Imaging Computing, Technical University of Munich (summa cum laude)</p>
      </article>
      <article class="item">
        <p>Graduate study/research in Medical Imaging and Informatics, IIT Kharagpur</p>
      </article>
      <article class="item">
        <p>B.E. in Electrical and Electronics Engineering, BITS Pilani</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section title="Selected Awards">
    <div class="list">
      <article class="item">
        <p>Medical Image Analysis Best Paper Award (2016): Metric Hashing Forests</p>
      </article>
      <article class="item">
        <p>MICCAI Young Scientist runner-up recognition (2017, public-profile evidence)</p>
      </article>
      <article class="item">
        <p>Siemens Healthineers recognition (2021): Successful Digital Health Inventor</p>
      </article>
      <article class="item">
        <p>Siemens Healthineers recognition (2021): Finalist, Most Innovative Project Award</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section title="Research Metrics and Publications">
    <div class="item">
      <p>
        Public profile checks in the research report indicate a broad publication record spanning
        medical image retrieval, neuroimaging, segmentation, robustness evaluation, and clinical AI.
      </p>
      <p>
        At report check time, ResearchGate listed 87 publication records and 4,260 citations. The
        report recommends deduplicated interpretation because profile-level counts may include
        preprint and final variants.
      </p>
      <p>
        Representative works include FastSurfer, QuickNAT, ReLayNet, FatSegNet, Metric Hashing
        Forests, and Deep Multiple Instance Hashing.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section title="Patents Summary">
    <div class="item">
      <p>
        Verified public patent portfolio includes six families in medical image metadata
        generation, image-data evaluation, cue-based reporting assistance, multimodal 2D image
        analysis, protocol data generation for radiology workflows, and real-time endoscopy scene
        analysis.
      </p>
      <p>
        Patent families are presented on the patents page in grouped form to avoid jurisdictional
        duplication.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section title="Skills and Competencies">
    <div class="item">
      <p>
        Medical image computing, clinical AI evaluation, workflow-oriented healthcare AI, regulated
        healthcare software, generative and agentic AI systems, retrieval-augmented workflows, AI
        product strategy, and cross-functional research-to-product translation.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  {hasCvPdf && (
    <Section title="Download">
      <div class="item">
        <p>
          <a href={cvPdfHref}>Download PDF CV</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </Section>
  )}
</BaseLayout>
